library(truchet)

Create a truchet tile:

tile_1 <- st_truchet_p(type = "d")

Create mosaic:

mosaic <- st_truchet_ms(tile_1)

Extract mosaic:

container <- mosaic[["container"]]
mosaic <- mosaic[["mosaic"]]
mosaic <- mosaic %>%
  mutate(id = 1:n())
ggplot() + 
  geom_sf(data = mosaic[28,])

Sample points:

pts <- data.frame(geometry = st_geometry(st_sample(mosaic %>%
                                                     filter(color == 1), 
                                                   size = 2500))) %>%
  st_as_sf() %>%
  st_set_agr("constant")

Plot:

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = mosaic) +
  geom_sf(data = pts)

Id points:

pts <- pts %>%
  st_join(mosaic %>% 
            select(id))

Plot:

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = mosaic) +
  geom_sf(data = pts %>%
            filter(id == 16))

Voronoi polygons:

v <- st_voronoi(pts %>% 
                  filter(id == 16) %>%
                  st_union()) %>% 
  st_collection_extract() %>%
  st_intersection(mosaic %>% 
                    filter(id == 16)) %>%
  st_sf() %>%
  mutate(id = 16,
         color = sample.int(10, n(), replace = TRUE))

Plot:

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = v)

Now do for all polygons:

v <- data.frame()
p_id <- mosaic %>%
  filter(color == 1) %>%
  pull(id)

count <- 0

for(i in p_id){
  count <- count +1
  v <- rbind(v,
             st_voronoi(pts %>% 
                  filter(id == i) %>%
                  st_union()) %>% 
  st_collection_extract() %>%
  st_intersection(mosaic %>% 
                    filter(id == i)) %>%
  st_sf() %>%
  mutate(id = i,
         color = sample.int(5, n(), replace = TRUE)))
}

st_agr(v) < "constant"

v <- cbind(v, 
           v %>% 
             st_centroid() %>%
             st_coordinates())

Plot:

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = v %>%
            mutate(color = sample.int(5, # Random colors across the board
                                      n(), 
                                      replace = TRUE) + 
                     rbinom(n(), # Random colors with a probability trend in function of X * Y
                            5, 
                            prob = 1 - (X * Y)/(max(X) * max(Y))),
                   color = round(color)),
          aes(fill = factor(color)))

Make pretty:

          fill = "white") +

                            5,

Voronoi polygons:

# Initialize data frame for voronoi polygons
v <- data.frame()

# Filter elements of the mosaic by color
p_id <- mosaic %>%
  filter(color == 1) %>%
  pull(id)

# Initialize count for colors
count <- 0

for(i in p_id){
  count <- count +1
  v <- rbind(v,
             st_voronoi(pts %>% 
                  filter(id == i) %>%
                  st_union()) %>% 
  st_collection_extract() %>%
  st_intersection(mosaic %>% 
                    filter(id == i)) %>%
  st_sf() %>%
  mutate(id = i,
         color = sample.int(5, n(), replace = TRUE)))
}

v <- cbind(v, 
           v %>% 
             st_centroid() %>%
             st_coordinates())
Warning in st_centroid.sf(.) :

Make pretty:

col_palette <- MexBrewer::mex.brewer("Frida", n = 10)

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = container,
          fill = "white",
          color = NA) +
  geom_sf(data = v %>%
            mutate(color = color + 
                     rbinom(n(), # Random colors with a probability trend in function of X * Y
                            5, 
                            prob = 1 - (X * Y)/(max(X) * max(Y))),
                   color = round(color)),
          aes(fill = factor(color)),
          color = "white") + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = col_palette) +
  theme_void() + 
  theme(legend.position = "none")

Make pretty:

col_palette <- MexBrewer::mex.brewer("Frida", n = 10)
col_palette_2 <- MexBrewer::mex.brewer("Aurora", n = 10)

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = v %>%
            mutate(color = color + 
                     rbinom(n(), # Random colors with a probability trend in function of X * Y
                            5, 
                            prob = 1 - (X * Y)/(max(X) * max(Y))),
                   color = round(color)),
          aes(fill = factor(color)),
          color = "white",
          size = 0.1) + 
   scale_fill_manual(values = col_palette) +
  new_scale("fill") +
  geom_sf(data = v_2 %>%
            mutate(color = color + 
                     rbinom(n(), # Random colors with a probability trend in function of X * Y
                            5, 
                            prob = (X * Y)/(max(X) * max(Y))),
                   color = round(color)),
          aes(fill = factor(color)),
          color = "white",
          size = 0.1) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = col_palette_2) +
  theme_void() + 
  theme(legend.position = "none")
